The ANCYL in Cape Town says it supports calls for legislation to combat racism. CAPE TOWN - The African National Congress Youth League (ANCYL) in Cape Town says it supports calls for legislation to combat racism.The youth movement's leaders met with owners of The Bungalow restaurant on Friday, following an incident in which two black patrons were offended when they were identified as &quot;2 blacks&quot; on their bill.They said discrimination against any race should not tolerated and that the party's youth structure would be for introducing a law that criminalises racism.The ANCYL s Unathi Tshotwana says: We ll interact with the motherboard and government to have harsh legislation to deal with racists, who want to take our country back to the apartheid years. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)